<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880405-0066 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Newmont Mining Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> NEM </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Newmont Mining Corp. retained Goldman, Sachs andamp; Co. to find buyers for Newmont Oil Co., a subsidiary that reported $40.5 million in pretax profit last year.    Newmont also said discussions on the sale of its 75% interest in Newmont Australia Ltd. had ended. Newmont had said in December it was trying to sell the interest.    Newmont has been selling assets to pay debt that resulted from its efforts to avoid a hostile takeover by Mesa Partners L.P. last year. Newmont borrowed to make a $2.2 billion dividend in 1987. Since the beginning of the year, Newmont has cut debt to $1.59 billion from $1.93 billion. </TEXT></DOC>